wikipedia_page.main: Adolphus Warburton Moore (1841–1887) (known generally as A. W. Moore) was a British civil servant and mountaineer.

response: *Adolphus Warburton Moore (A. W. Moore), British civil servant and mountaineer (1841–1887)

The summit was first reached on 23 July 1862 by H. B. George and Adolphus Warburton Moore, with guides Christian Almer and Ulrich Kaufmann. They used what is now the normal route, the south-west ridge.Helmut Dumler,Willi P. Burkhardt, Les 4000 des Alpes,
